023package com.restfb.types;
024
025import com.restfb.BinaryAttachment;
026
027/**
028 * Attachment object for uploading a Reel to Facebook.
029 *
030 * <p>
031 * use {@code withByteContent} for sending a binary attachment and {@code withUrl} if the URL is given instead
032 */
033public class FacebookReelAttachment extends BinaryAttachment {
034  private String reelUrl;
035
036  protected FacebookReelAttachment(byte[] byteData) {
037    data = byteData;
038  }
039
040  protected FacebookReelAttachment(String reelUrl) {
041    this.reelUrl = reelUrl;
042  }
043
044  public static FacebookReelAttachment withByteContent(byte[] reelData) {
045    return new FacebookReelAttachment(reelData);
046  }
047
048  public static FacebookReelAttachment withUrl(String reelUrl) {
049    return new FacebookReelAttachment(reelUrl);
050  }
051
052  @Override
053  public boolean isFacebookReel() {
054    return true;
055  }
056
057  public boolean isBinary() {
058    return data != null;
059  }
060
061  public int getFileSizeInBytes() {
062    if (data != null) {
063      return data.length;
064    }
065    return 0;
066  }
067
068  @java.lang.SuppressWarnings("all")
069  public String getReelUrl() {
070    return this.reelUrl;
071  }
072}
